AN ACT relating to natural resources; authorizing the Joint Interim
Standing Committee on Natural Resources to evaluate
and review issues relating to water conservation;
requiring the Division of Environmental Protection of the
State Department of Conservation and Natural Resources
to conduct an interim study on artificial turf and synthetic
grass; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Joint Interim Standing Committee on Natural
2 Resources and sets forth the powers and duties of the Committee. (NRS 218E.320,
3 218E.330) Section 1 of this bill authorizes the Committee to evaluate and review
4 issues relating to water conservation.
5 Section 2 of this bill requires the Division of Environmental Protection of the
6 State Department of Conservation and Natural Resources to: (1) conduct an interim
7 study during the 2025-2026 legislative interim on artificial turf and synthetic grass;
8 and (2) on or before August 1, 2026, submit a report of its findings and
9 recommendations to the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau for transmittal
10 to the 84th Session of the Nevada Legislature.
